payload.message:
Tailwind was never “seeing” the utility classes from the shared components, so `bg-red-100` got purged. In `template/web/astro/src/styles/global.css:4-5` I rewired the `@source` directives to cover the local Astro files and the actual monorepo path `../../../../../packages/...`. The previous target (`../../../../packages/...`) stopped one directory too early (`template/packages`), so Tailwind never scanned `packages/ui/shadcn/components`.

Build now succeeds with those sources loaded (`npm run build`). To confirm the background class at runtime, restart the dev server with `npm run dev`.

content.text:
Tailwind was never “seeing” the utility classes from the shared components, so `bg-red-100` got purged. In `template/web/astro/src/styles/global.css:4-5` I rewired the `@source` directives to cover the local Astro files and the actual monorepo path `../../../../../packages/...`. The previous target (`../../../../packages/...`) stopped one directory too early (`template/packages`), so Tailwind never scanned `packages/ui/shadcn/components`.

Build now succeeds with those sources loaded (`npm run build`). To confirm the background class at runtime, restart the dev server with `npm run dev`.
